&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Assembler&lt;/strong&gt; role is focused on building doors and frames and reports to the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Production Supervisor.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is perfect for an individual who &lt;strong&gt;has attention to detail (safety, quality, efficiency), strong work ethic/reliability, and is a problem solver&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp; A vital member of the &lt;strong&gt;Fabrication Department,&lt;/strong&gt; this is an opportunity to build a career with an industry leader.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job responsibilities include: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Read job specifications to determine machine adjustments and material requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform general fabrication and assembly of doors using hand and power tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drill holes and prepare materials according to work orders, fabrication sheets, and schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure workpiece dimensions and conduct quality inspections to ensure accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure parts meet specifications by following prints, worksheets, and shop drawings while completing tasks with minimal supervision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Are Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using power tools, machinery, and reading a tape measure (to 1/16”).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read and interpret fabrication drawings and perform basic math.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively multitask, prioritize, and meet deadlines in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with team members and communicate clearly with peers and management; flexible to work varied schedules and cross-train as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An uncompromising safety-first approach in the workplace.&amp;nbsp; At OBE we have each other’s back&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What OBE&amp;nbsp;Offers You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
