&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Highlights &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1st shift – Full Time – 4:45 AM – 3:15 PM&amp;nbsp;Mon-Thurs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2nd shift – Full Time – 3:15 AM – 1:45 PM Mon-Thurs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Friday OT to be determined by business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shift length may vary on occasion based on production needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Get To Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Assembler plays a key role in the manufacturing of high-quality windows and glass products. This hands-on position involves assembling window systems, installing components, applying sealants, and inspecting finished units for quality. Assemblers work on flow line and bench production stations, contributing to a collaborative team environment where safety, precision, and quality are paramount.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set up production stations according to job specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate air-powered tools and departmental machinery to assemble components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean, seal, and apply weather stripping to windows and frames.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use tape measures, drills, and other tools to install hardware and glass.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fabricate and hang sashes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform quality checks on assembled products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Load and prepare items for shipping and production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a clean and organized work area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow company quality standards and standard operating procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and support team efforts as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in OSHA safety training and follow all PPE &amp;amp; JSA guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
