&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;CNC Programmer&lt;/strong&gt; is focused on &lt;strong&gt;entering all custom patterns into the CAD system for production, interpreting and entering sketches to be produced, assisting with scheduling, and supporting team members &lt;/strong&gt;and reports to the Fabrication Supervisor&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is perfect for an individual who&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;is self- driven, organized and quality focused&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp; A vital member of the &lt;strong&gt;Production Administration Department&lt;/strong&gt;, this is an opportunity to build a career with an industry leader.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job responsibilities include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Entering all custom patterns into the Computer Aided Design (CAD) System&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpret and enter sketches to be produced by our CNC Operators&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate Computer Aided Design (CAD) System&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Are Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Auto-CAD (2005 or later) Training Certificate with 2-4 years of work experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must possess the ability to read and interpret contract drawings and customer sketches as well as the ability to create and modify drawings in CAD/CAM software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have high mathematic and logical aptitude, especially with fractions and decimals as a unit of measure (millimeters and inches)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accuracy in data entry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be highly detail oriented and can solve problems with minimal guidance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter, motivated with ability to complete projects on time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
