&lt;p&gt;The Continuous Improvement Engineer is a key member of the Operational Excellence team, focused on stabilizing and advancing manufacturing processes across the business. This role partners cross-functionally to design, implement, and sustain operating systems that improve cost, quality, and delivery performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leveraging Lean, Six Sigma, and Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP), you will lead the development of standardized processes, enhance supplier and customer value streams, and drive consistency across operations. You will play an active role in embedding Toyota Production System principles moving the organization from foundational understanding to effective, sustained application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Manager of Operational Excellence, this position works alongside a team of operational experts to translate complex challenges into structured, scalable solutions that strengthen overall business performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
