&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement standardized processes and documentation, including Standard Work, Process Flow Diagrams (PFD), PFMEA, Control Plans, and Job Element Sheets, ensuring consistency, scalability, and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply structured problem-solving methodologies (A3, 5-Why, cause-and-effect analysis, logic trees) to diagnose root causes and implement sustainable countermeasures for complex operational challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support New Product Introduction (NPI) by ensuring process readiness, validation, and alignment with manufacturing capabilities, including development of quality systems and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and execute testing and validation plans, including gauge studies, reliability and repeatability testing, and statistical analysis, ensuring process capability and product quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize data-driven performance management to monitor results, validate improvements, and sustain operational gains across manufacturing systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage training systems and documentation to build workforce capability, reinforce standardization, and ensure compliance across operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support capital investment initiatives, including preparation of AFE (Authorization for Expenditure) documentation to justify process improvements and operational enhancements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct and publish operational audits, identify performance gaps, and lead follow-up actions to resolve inconsistencies and quality concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate voice of the customer insights into improvement initiatives, aligning operational performance with customer expectations and value delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
